[recto] 50. Witt Library. P.B.II. Quarrel at Cards: a) With the same background of cottages with a crowd of people in the central street; 1) Thomée Coll., Altena, Luthmer 1931 [= Kurt Luthmer (Hrsg.), Die Sammlung Thomée, Marburg an der Lahn: Verlag des Kunstgeschichtlichen Seminars, 1931], N° 102, Eichenholz 40 x 56,5 cm, Bez. P. BREVGHEL 1622; 2) Sale Lepke, 10 May 1921, N° 106, Holz bez. und datiert 1622, 40 x 54 cm; 3) New York, Metropolitan Museum, signed P.BRVEGEL 1619, wood 283/4 x 401/2 in. (73,1 x 102,9 cm) ex. Comte Conet de Ways Ruart de Vaneck, Brussels; Cutting from catal. photograph; [verso] 4) De Fursac Sale, Fiévez, Brussels, 14-15 Dec. 1923, N° 33 signé et daté 1620; 5) Berlin Museums Sale, Munich 9-10 June 1937, N°681, Eiche 74,5 x 105,5 cm; [toegevoegde vermelding]: 'F.G. schön und frei. An der Bank rechts bez. P. BRVEGHEL; 6) Johnson Coll. Philadelphia, Panel 133/4 x 211/2 cm; b) Same background with an empty street, Wattecamps Sale, Mak, Dordrecht, 15-16 May 1934, Panel 53 x 66 cm; c) Under Teniers: without cards on ground. The same landscape in background, but different foliage. Ehrich Sale, American Art Association, New York 18-19 April 1934, N° 50, craddled panel 301/2 x38 cm as Rubens & David Teniers the younger.
